		     'embed' example for elastiC
		     ===========================

INTRODUCTION
------------

elastiC is a portable high-level object-oriented interpreted language
with a C like syntax.
This package provide an example of how to embed elastiC in a C
application.

USAGE
-----

To compile the example, simply issue the commands:

  % configure
  % make

This will build the `embed' program and the `embedded.ecc' compiled
elastiC module.
Then to try it, execute the `embed' program.
This will dynamically load the `embedded.ecc' module and subsequently
call the `runme' function contained therein, passing it some arguments
and printing the result.

ELASTIC WEB SITE
----------------

